ToDo's for the WIDS/WIPS framework
==================================

Following is a rather incomplete list of possible extensions/improvements to the framework:

General
-------

* Adding more detection, prevention and output templates

* Executing performance tests and improving speed

* Improving exception handling (e.g. more exception classes, escalate exceptions to a single caller)

* Improving documentation of modules and functions (e.g. with doxygen or ReST markup instead of docstrings)

* Implementing management GUI for controlling framework and editing configuration (e.g. signature editor)

* Reducing dependance on external libraries (e.g. re-implement TST algorithm)

* Refactoring XML parsing of templates

Capture
-------

* Implementing auto-configuration of network interfaces (e.g. via ioctl())

Prevention
----------

* Enhancing frame crafting capabilities of executor module

Output
---------

* Implementing IDMEF ouput template

* Implementing syslog output template